	dprr:hasNoteText "Accused of incest with Catiline. Catiline was accused by Clodius and acquitted with the help of Catulus, while Fabia is probably one of the Vestals who were defended by Pupius Piso and acquitted (Cic. Tog. Cand., and Ascon. 91 C; Plut. Cat. Min. 19.3; Oros. 6.3.1; cf. Cic. Brut. 236; Cat. 3.9; Q. Cic. Comm. Pet. 10; Sall. Cat. 15.1; see 74, Additional Note)." .
